WRITING.TEXT:
 The *Arthur Newman* issue, as a redditor [previously described](https://www.reddit.com/r/PleX/comments/3qj1ii/heres_how_you_can_get_rid_of_arthur_newman_from/):

 Whenever Plex sees a file named `RARBG.com.mp4`, it likes to match it up with a movie named *Arthur Newman* for some reason. That file is actually just a little trailer thing for the RARBG release group, and it's included with a lot of movies.

 nbsp;

`RARBG.com.mp4` is in my .plexignore file as follows, which is [in my root movies directory](http://i.imgur.com/7GirrqC.png) (rest of file is copied over from [Plex's sample](https://support.plex.tv/hc/en-us/articles/201375253-Excluding-New-Content-with-plexignore) and mostly commented out):
 \# Ignore RARBG vid

RARBG.com.mp4

 nbsp;

\# Ignore all files with "trailer" in the name

\*trailer*

 nbsp;

\# Ignore files with the extension ".cr2"

\# *.cr2

 nbsp;

\# Ignore directories called "Modified"

\# Modified/*

 nbsp;

\# Ignore all ".tif" files in the "thumbnails" subdirectory

\# thumbnails/*.tif

 nbsp;

I've scanned the library, I've refreshed, I still keeping seeing *Arthur Newman*s the Plex web UI. I've also tried variations on the name including `*RARBG.com.mp4`, `*RARBG.com*` and probably a few others. Any help?
